# Shared UI Components Localization (Arabic RTL)

## Goal Description
The standard shared components (`FiltersBar`, `DataTable`, `ExportButtons`, `SideDrawer`) are already structurally built and working. However, they currently have hardcoded **English text** strings inside them, whereas the UI Specification dictates **Primary Language: Arabic (RTL) with English fallback**. 

This plan will update the internal defaults of these shared components to match the Arabic requirement.

## Proposed Changes

### [MODIFY] `FiltersBar.tsx`
- Change default search placeholder to `بحث...` (Search...).
- Change department filter default label to `القسم` (Department).
- Translate department options: `الهندسة`, `المبيعات`, `المنتج`, إلخ.
- Change Status filter label to `الحالة` and options to `نشط`, `غير نشط`, `قيد الانتظار`.
- Change Date range label to `الفترة الزمنية`.
- Change Reset button text to `إعادة ضبط`.

### [MODIFY] `ExportButtons.tsx`
- Change "Exporting..." text to `جاري التصدير...`.

### [MODIFY] `DataTable.tsx`
- Change the generic default `emptyMessage` from "No data available" to `لا توجد بيانات متاحة`.
- Ensure pagination defaults have the Arabic strings `السابق` and `التالي` as the primary visible elements for RTL.

### [MODIFY] `SideDrawer.tsx`
- Ensure the drawer respects `side="right"` as the absolute default for RTL layouts to slide in from the correct directional edge according to Arabic UX patterns.

## Verification Plan
1. Ensure the TypeScript compiler `npm run build` succeeds after these changes.
2. Confirm the UI components dynamically use the new labels.
